WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:08.008
[hard rock music playing]

00:21.771 --> 00:23.106
Okay, you were right.

00:23.898 --> 00:24.983
We're not talking.

00:25.066 --> 00:27.027
I'm still extremely mad at you.

00:28.445 --> 00:30.030
Fine. Then I'm still mad at you, too.

00:30.238 --> 00:31.072
Great.

00:31.614 --> 00:34.200
-Your hair looks stupid by the way.
-[gasps]

00:34.284 --> 00:35.118
Your...

00:35.827 --> 00:36.661
face looks bad.

00:36.745 --> 00:38.997
-No, it doesn't. My face rules.
-Whatever!

00:39.080 --> 00:41.332
[both growl]

00:42.709 --> 00:43.710
[tires screech]

00:48.006 --> 00:49.716
-[Debbie gasps]
-Thank the Lord!

00:49.799 --> 00:52.761
Glad you're alive, but oh, boy,
are you dead meat.

00:52.844 --> 00:54.471
Your father and I have been sick,
worried about y'all,

00:54.554 --> 00:56.848
and you did not even have
the decency to answer your cell phones!

00:56.931 --> 00:58.266
-Cell phones are a privilege!
-That is right!

00:58.349 --> 01:00.143
Mom, Dad, cut the crap.

01:00.226 --> 01:01.895
-Blair, do not sass me!
-Yeah, cut the crap!

01:01.978 --> 01:02.896
[Anderson gasps]

01:02.979 --> 01:04.397
-Sterling!
-Sterling.

01:04.481 --> 01:05.690
What has gotten into you, young lady?

01:05.774 --> 01:08.026
We know about you!
The real whole dang serious truth!

01:08.109 --> 01:10.570
Yes, and where to begin, Mom?

01:10.653 --> 01:11.529
Well, let's see.

01:11.613 --> 01:13.198
You're not from Savannah,

01:13.281 --> 01:15.200
you're from Nandina, Georgia.

01:15.867 --> 01:18.953
Where you belong to
Tabernacle Church of Christ the Reindeer--

01:19.037 --> 01:20.622
-Redeemer, Redeemer...
-Redeemer!

01:20.830 --> 01:24.167
Where you might be sad to learnÂ that
one of your childhood snakes just died.

01:24.709 --> 01:28.254
And, oh, yeah, you're wanted
for first-degree arson!

01:28.338 --> 01:30.381
That's enough, Blair! That's enough.

01:31.174 --> 01:33.176
Mom, you have to tell us the truth.

01:38.765 --> 01:39.599
All right, yes.

01:40.600 --> 01:45.522
Yes, I have not been entirely truthful
about my past.

01:45.605 --> 01:46.439
[scoffs]

01:46.523 --> 01:49.984
But it was because she--
we needed to protect you.

01:50.068 --> 01:50.902
From what?

01:52.320 --> 01:54.405
All right, girls. Just listen. It...

01:55.198 --> 01:57.075
It was a different time in my life.

01:58.159 --> 02:00.537
I was very young and impressionable

02:00.620 --> 02:02.997
and I fell in with an extreme crowd,

02:04.124 --> 02:06.167
and I acted out of hate, not love.

02:06.459 --> 02:07.877
And that is not what God intended.

02:09.087 --> 02:10.088
I can see that now.

02:10.171 --> 02:11.214
So, you did this.

02:11.297 --> 02:13.007
You set fire to an abortion clinic!

02:14.050 --> 02:15.677
That is not very Christian of you!

02:15.760 --> 02:16.594
No.

02:17.387 --> 02:19.097
But at the time,
I thought it was very Christian.

02:19.180 --> 02:20.014
[scoffs]

02:20.098 --> 02:22.016
Obviously, I was wrong.

02:22.851 --> 02:24.727
-Was anyone hurt?
-No. No.

02:24.811 --> 02:26.479
Thank the Lord. No one was hurt.

02:26.938 --> 02:28.148
This is not an excuse

02:28.606 --> 02:31.484
because we should always
take responsibility for our actions,

02:31.943 --> 02:33.736
but I was acting under the influence

02:33.820 --> 02:37.991
of some very persuasive people.

02:39.450 --> 02:42.453
They were saying, uh,
provocative things about the Lord,

02:42.537 --> 02:44.122
things that are not true

02:44.581 --> 02:45.957
knowing God the way I do now,

02:46.457 --> 02:49.002
how he forgives and loves all people.

02:50.837 --> 02:52.797
I'm ashamed I fell so far off the path.

02:57.927 --> 02:59.053
Who are these people?

03:00.555 --> 03:01.598
Were you in a cult?

03:01.973 --> 03:02.974
Why did you do it?

03:03.057 --> 03:04.142
Are people after you?

03:04.225 --> 03:05.685
Did the police question you?

03:05.768 --> 03:07.770
-Did you feel cool in the moment?
-Blair!

03:07.854 --> 03:09.189
Girls, the details are not important.

03:09.272 --> 03:11.774
What you need to know is
that from the moment we had you,

03:11.858 --> 03:13.151
we have done everything in our power

03:13.234 --> 03:16.321
to make sure that you do not wind up
like I did those many years ago.

03:18.323 --> 03:19.157
All right, we have--

03:20.742 --> 03:22.243
We have worked so hard...

03:23.578 --> 03:24.621
to give you this life.

03:25.788 --> 03:26.748
We both have.

03:32.420 --> 03:34.797
-Are you in danger?
-Are we safe?

03:35.340 --> 03:37.717
I'm not in danger and we are safe.

03:38.718 --> 03:40.970
We have a plan, and lawyers.

03:41.054 --> 03:41.888
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

03:41.971 --> 03:44.390
-And everything is gonna be just fine.
-Yeah.

03:48.519 --> 03:49.938
[exhales deeply] Okay.

03:50.021 --> 03:51.189
[chuckles] Wow.

03:51.272 --> 03:53.733
Our, uh-- Our big family secret is out.

03:53.816 --> 03:55.276
-It is a lot...
-A lot.

03:55.360 --> 03:56.819
...but it's out, there it is.

03:57.528 --> 03:58.905
So, here's what we're gonna do.

03:59.948 --> 04:03.326
[sniffs]
I am gonna pack y'all some snacks to-go

04:03.409 --> 04:04.994
while you put on your PJs,

04:05.078 --> 04:07.288
and y'all are gonna go
to that lock-in tonight

04:07.372 --> 04:10.333
and enjoy being teenagers
while you still can.

04:12.085 --> 04:13.836
All right. Come on, girls, let's go.
Chop chop!

04:13.920 --> 04:14.921
Hummus and veggies?

04:15.004 --> 04:16.589
-And Oreos.
-Yeah.

04:16.673 --> 04:18.549
Oh. All right. Go, go, go.

04:19.509 --> 04:20.468
[chuckles]

04:21.302 --> 04:23.972
[theme music]

04:24.055 --> 04:26.349
[vocalizing]

05:04.387 --> 05:06.431
I need cash to deposit,
our bank account is low.

05:07.140 --> 05:07.974
Why?

05:08.433 --> 05:10.727
Gas, lock-in pizza.

05:10.810 --> 05:11.644
Fine.

05:13.813 --> 05:14.647
How much?

05:15.023 --> 05:15.857
Two hundred.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.283
So...

05:27.285 --> 05:28.119
So.

05:29.954 --> 05:31.331
Mom's a wanted fugitive.

05:31.956 --> 05:34.125
Mom is a wanted fugitive, happy Friday.

05:37.170 --> 05:38.713
It's like she was living
this whole double life

05:38.796 --> 05:39.756
that we didn't know about.

05:39.839 --> 05:42.342
We can't exactly judge her.
We're living a double life, too.

05:43.760 --> 05:45.178
Putting bad guys away.

05:45.887 --> 05:47.555
She was being a bad guy.

05:51.059 --> 05:52.018
Is that lip gloss?

05:53.394 --> 05:54.228
Oh.

05:54.312 --> 05:56.481
You're really pulling out
all the stops for April.

05:56.564 --> 05:59.150
Shove it. I want to look nice tonight,
in general.

06:00.485 --> 06:01.319
You're not gonna bail, right?

06:02.570 --> 06:04.697
I kind of need you there
with the whole me and April situation,

06:04.781 --> 06:06.657
for, like, moral support.

06:06.741 --> 06:09.744
Bailing is your thing, not mine.

06:11.454 --> 06:13.206
[cell phones bleep]

06:23.716 --> 06:25.176
Is he even here?

06:26.135 --> 06:28.763
-Girls.
-Bowser, what's happening?

06:28.846 --> 06:30.515
No offense, but we're slammed.

06:30.598 --> 06:32.350
I have 30 pizzas that are about to go live

06:32.433 --> 06:33.684
and I gotta be there when they land.

06:35.728 --> 06:36.771
Why do y'all work for me?

06:37.730 --> 06:38.731
Uh...

06:38.815 --> 06:41.025
You said you needed money
to fix your daddy's truck.

06:42.151 --> 06:43.903
You got that taken care of weeks ago.

06:45.530 --> 06:46.447
Yeah.

06:52.578 --> 06:54.455
-[Bowser] Hm?
-Wait! No, Bowser, that's not--

06:54.539 --> 06:55.873
It's, like, not what you think.

06:55.957 --> 06:57.583
How could you have known this whole time,

06:57.667 --> 07:00.670
and not told me that
your mama was some nutjob fugitive?

07:00.753 --> 07:03.256
Is that why you got in this business
in the first place, hm?

07:03.339 --> 07:05.174
To learn how to help somebody
evade the law?

07:05.258 --> 07:07.135
No, we didn't know, we promise.

07:07.218 --> 07:09.011
We just found out, like, today.

07:09.095 --> 07:10.555
Yeah, and our mom is not a nutjob.

07:10.638 --> 07:12.598
She only made a mistake,
like, a long time ago.

07:12.682 --> 07:15.184
How am I supposed to believe you?
You're a couple of liars.

07:15.268 --> 07:16.352
That is a nasty allegation.

07:16.436 --> 07:17.520
Never to you, Bowser.

07:19.188 --> 07:20.314
Really?

07:21.315 --> 07:22.358
[exhales deeply]

07:22.442 --> 07:24.068
Your folks came to see me yesterday,

07:24.152 --> 07:25.278
looking for you two.

07:26.779 --> 07:27.822
Lyin' is bad.

07:29.031 --> 07:30.408
But lying to your family...

07:32.243 --> 07:33.202
that's unforgivable.

07:33.286 --> 07:34.662
No, but we only skipped school

07:34.745 --> 07:36.497
so that we could figure out
what's going on with our mom.

07:36.581 --> 07:38.749
We swear we didn't know about her before.

07:38.833 --> 07:40.668
I ain't got time for all your excuses.

07:40.751 --> 07:43.546
This shit done got too complicated
with the two of you.

07:43.629 --> 07:46.716
Now I'm playing boss
and babysitter and bestie, apparently.

07:48.593 --> 07:50.386
You didn't have to answer my call today.

07:50.803 --> 07:51.971
I know I didn't have to.

07:52.555 --> 07:54.724
I'm not blaming you, I'm blaming myself.

07:57.727 --> 07:59.145
Running with y'all got me soft.

07:59.770 --> 08:01.481
So soft, I threw a skip.

08:02.106 --> 08:06.235
It reminded me why
I only look out for myself, and that's it!

08:06.319 --> 08:09.780
Well, I think
that's a really shitty approach to life.

08:09.864 --> 08:11.991
[Bowser] Yeah, well,
why don't you finish high school

08:12.074 --> 08:13.910
before you talk to me about life?

08:14.827 --> 08:15.661
Hm?

08:17.914 --> 08:18.748
You're fired.

08:20.166 --> 08:21.876
-We're fired?
-Mm-hm.

08:22.543 --> 08:25.004
Just because we're, like,
friends with you?

08:25.087 --> 08:26.464
No! You're fired because

08:26.547 --> 08:29.091
I should have never got involved with you
in the first place!

08:29.509 --> 08:31.844
A couple of kids in pajamas, even.

08:32.970 --> 08:34.847
I was doing just fine.

08:35.765 --> 08:38.935
And you came in
and you convinced me to change things.

08:39.018 --> 08:40.186
You mean be happy?

08:40.269 --> 08:41.103
Happy?

08:41.896 --> 08:43.356
Do I look happy to you, right now?

08:44.148 --> 08:44.982
No.

08:45.066 --> 08:45.900
No.

08:46.567 --> 08:49.278
And the mochi on the motherfucking
non-fat yogurt sundae...

08:50.696 --> 08:54.700
Now, I know the whereabouts
of a wanted fugitive.

08:54.784 --> 08:56.077
You're not gonna turn our mom in, are you?

08:57.787 --> 08:58.663
No.

08:59.664 --> 09:00.831
I'm not going to turn her in.

09:01.999 --> 09:03.084
Because of you!

09:04.085 --> 09:06.504
Because you put me
in an impossible situation here.

09:08.089 --> 09:10.258
So, now I'm forced to forgo my ethics

09:10.716 --> 09:12.677
and leave 90,000 dollars on the table.

09:13.094 --> 09:14.595
So, yeah, sorry, girls.

09:15.221 --> 09:16.973
I'm gonna need you to get up out of here.

09:18.849 --> 09:19.809
Now!

09:31.070 --> 09:32.238
[Blair sighs]

09:33.614 --> 09:34.448
Are you okay?

09:36.117 --> 09:36.951
Yeah.

09:38.035 --> 09:39.078
Just, you know...

09:40.955 --> 09:41.956
rejected.

09:42.498 --> 09:43.332
Again.

09:51.173 --> 09:53.759
I've been thinking about
what you said in Nandina.

09:55.469 --> 09:57.680
About me creating drama, or whatever.

09:57.763 --> 10:00.391
I'm sorry I said all that stuff, Blair,
but you said mean stuff, too.

10:00.850 --> 10:03.352
That you have blonde hair
and that you're gonna go to UGA?

10:03.686 --> 10:04.520
Yeah.

10:04.937 --> 10:06.897
Whoo. How will you ever forgive me?

10:06.981 --> 10:08.107
You said I was boring.

10:09.775 --> 10:11.193
You were harsh and you know it.

10:11.277 --> 10:12.528
Well, I was pissed, okay?

10:16.866 --> 10:19.118
But what sucks and makes me want to...

10:19.702 --> 10:21.329
punch you in the face, lightly...

10:23.164 --> 10:24.582
is that, uh...

10:28.753 --> 10:30.129
I think you're kinda right.

10:34.342 --> 10:35.343
I'd rather...

10:37.011 --> 10:39.180
stir things up, so...

10:40.514 --> 10:43.100
life feels bad because of my actions,

10:45.227 --> 10:46.187
rather than...

10:49.815 --> 10:52.943
just life... feeling bad.

10:55.029 --> 10:59.533
And I want to want
to go with you to the lock-in, but...

11:01.160 --> 11:02.411
I just don't.

11:05.498 --> 11:06.874
I want to be with Miles.

11:10.503 --> 11:11.754
I think I love him.

11:13.089 --> 11:13.964
Oh.

11:15.049 --> 11:17.259
Blair, it's gonna be really hard,

11:18.052 --> 11:20.304
and it's gonna take some time,

11:20.763 --> 11:23.099
but you're gonna get over it.

11:23.182 --> 11:24.183
Like I did with Luke.

11:25.476 --> 11:27.895
I don't love him the way you loved Luke.

11:30.898 --> 11:33.567
I love him the way Luke loves you.

11:35.861 --> 11:37.279
Oh. Um...

11:39.073 --> 11:39.949
Wow.

11:40.616 --> 11:41.742
That's the real deal.

11:43.869 --> 11:44.704
Yeah.

11:47.665 --> 11:52.378
Is it for you with... April?

11:53.254 --> 11:54.255
I don't know.

11:55.464 --> 11:56.424
It could be.

11:57.091 --> 11:59.385
[chuckles]
Soon you'll be scissoring our enemy.

12:00.010 --> 12:01.721
Girls don't actually scissor each other.

12:02.263 --> 12:03.097
What do they do?

12:03.180 --> 12:05.224
I don't know, but I guess I'll find out.

12:07.351 --> 12:11.230
You know I don't care
if you're, like, gay, or whatever.

12:11.647 --> 12:13.023
I'm more undefined than that.

12:13.816 --> 12:14.650
Like...

12:15.860 --> 12:17.987
if sexuality was a color wheel,

12:18.237 --> 12:23.284
I'd be in the blue-pink-purple part.

12:23.367 --> 12:24.994
I said, "Or whatever."

12:25.077 --> 12:27.037
You could bang a ficus, for all I care,

12:27.121 --> 12:29.832
just don't hide stuff.

12:30.750 --> 12:32.543
-Twin swear.
-Twin swear.

12:34.336 --> 12:35.588
Okay. [sniffs]

12:37.214 --> 12:38.924
[exhales deeply] Time to go get your girl.

12:39.341 --> 12:40.676
Time to get yours-- boy.

12:41.135 --> 12:42.511
No...  [sighs] ...Sterling.

12:43.929 --> 12:46.807
[sighs] He dumped me.
I'm not gonna go to him.

12:47.099 --> 12:48.100
You love him, right?

12:48.559 --> 12:51.896
Like, the full, real,
sick to your stomach kind of love?

12:51.979 --> 12:55.441
Yeah. Like--
Like I want to throw up all the time.

12:55.524 --> 12:57.234
Then you've gotta tell him how you feel.

12:57.318 --> 12:59.278
Okay? Life is too short to love in secret.

12:59.779 --> 13:01.489
"The truth will set you free."

13:02.031 --> 13:03.449
Oh, no, no.

13:04.200 --> 13:05.951
Love has made you too cheesy.

13:14.627 --> 13:16.879
Drive safe. Don't get pulled over,

13:16.962 --> 13:19.465
and call the second
you get across the border.

13:28.140 --> 13:29.183
[tires screech]

13:29.725 --> 13:32.186
-[Blair] Good luck!
-You, too. Bye!

13:42.905 --> 13:43.781
Oh!

13:43.864 --> 13:46.242
Thank the high, beautiful Heavens
you are here, Sterling.

13:46.325 --> 13:50.538
[groans] Coach Esposito has athlete's foot
running up and down both his legs,

13:50.621 --> 13:51.789
so I'm flying solo.

13:51.872 --> 13:53.165
People showed up early,

13:53.249 --> 13:54.917
April texted me that she's running late,

13:55.000 --> 13:56.710
and now Hannah B and Ezequiel

13:56.794 --> 13:59.004
are having a little bit
of a power struggle.

13:59.505 --> 14:00.339
What for?

14:00.422 --> 14:02.925
Over whether we're watching
Prince of Egypt

14:03.008 --> 14:05.052
or Davey and Goliath's
Snowboard Christmas.

14:05.344 --> 14:07.137
I prefer Prince of Egypt myself,

14:07.221 --> 14:09.098
so I can save Davey and Goliath
for the holidays with my nana,

14:09.181 --> 14:11.475
but I have been getting emails
from parents

14:11.559 --> 14:13.310
who are concerned that this lock-in

14:13.394 --> 14:15.688
is gonna promote sexual activity.

14:16.605 --> 14:18.524
And that animated Moses,

14:18.607 --> 14:22.194
I mean, he certainly promotes
something deep within, right?

14:22.278 --> 14:24.613
With the dark hair and the bronze calves,

14:24.697 --> 14:26.574
so I don't know what to do.

14:26.657 --> 14:27.741
It's your call.

14:28.784 --> 14:29.869
Um...

14:29.952 --> 14:31.787
-Prince of Egypt.
-Okay.

14:32.037 --> 14:35.624
Yes. Because I had a hard time
really believing

14:35.708 --> 14:39.336
that you kids would ever
be thinking about sexual activity

14:39.420 --> 14:41.839
at an innocent event
like an overnight lock-in.

14:41.922 --> 14:44.008
[all chattering]

14:48.888 --> 14:50.472
-Hi.
-Hey.

14:50.556 --> 14:51.473
Look, see?

14:51.557 --> 14:53.726
This is just good, clean fun.

14:54.310 --> 14:57.229
Um, I'm gonna double check
and see if the scavenger hunt clues

14:57.313 --> 14:58.689
-are all in the right places.
-Okay.

14:58.772 --> 15:00.065
[Sterling] I'll be back in a few.

15:05.237 --> 15:06.614
Oh, wow.

15:06.697 --> 15:08.365
I love your PJs, Lorna.

15:11.535 --> 15:12.369
Hi.

15:12.703 --> 15:13.746
Well, there you are.

15:13.829 --> 15:16.665
-Sorry, family stuff.
-Okay.

15:17.791 --> 15:19.501
Willingham students,

15:19.585 --> 15:22.171
welcome to the 12th annual

15:22.254 --> 15:24.715
Willingham Academy overnight lock-in!

15:24.798 --> 15:26.675
[all cheer]

15:28.260 --> 15:30.095
Now, I'm excited to announce

15:30.638 --> 15:34.642
that the doors are officially locked
from the inside.

15:38.604 --> 15:40.272
-Fire! Fire!
-[girl] Where?

15:41.065 --> 15:42.858
[muffled giggling]

15:42.942 --> 15:43.943
I got you guys.

15:44.026 --> 15:44.902
I'm just kiddin'!

15:44.985 --> 15:46.987
-[students groan]
-Oh, I love y'all.

15:48.822 --> 15:50.366
[cell phone rings]

15:52.034 --> 15:52.868
Hello.

15:52.952 --> 15:54.995
-Hey, when you gonna get here?
-[rock music playing]

15:55.079 --> 15:56.121
An hour.

15:56.413 --> 15:57.247
Okay.

15:58.082 --> 15:59.416
Vamos, amiga.

15:59.667 --> 16:00.542
Okay.

16:00.960 --> 16:02.586
[disconnects call]

16:09.802 --> 16:11.595
[tapping on cell phone]

16:11.679 --> 16:13.806
Lock-in pizza, get it while it's hot.

16:16.141 --> 16:17.142
[chuckles]

16:34.827 --> 16:37.830
[Hanna B] The movie should start at 11
when people have finished their pizza.

16:37.913 --> 16:39.289
And what will they do while they eat?

16:39.373 --> 16:41.500
Listen to all the chewing,
stare into each other's eyeballs?

16:41.583 --> 16:43.460
Maybe they'll have
meaningful conversations

16:43.544 --> 16:45.170
with their friends, Ezequiel.

16:45.254 --> 16:46.630
I wouldn't know what that's like.

16:46.714 --> 16:48.549
Hey, guys. Have you seen April?

16:48.632 --> 16:50.384
Uh, she snagged the good sleeping corner.

16:50.467 --> 16:51.885
Typically, seniors get that.

16:51.969 --> 16:53.178
She must have pulled some strings.

16:55.889 --> 16:57.850
