[sighs] Well...

33:32.301 --> 33:34.846
Alright, while ago I did something
a lot of people didn't like.

33:34.929 --> 33:36.889
But I-- you know,
I still think it's the right thing.

33:37.306 --> 33:40.560
But we knew the police would not agree,

33:40.643 --> 33:43.021
so I've had to lay low.

33:43.104 --> 33:44.647
So, you're, like, a criminal?

33:46.649 --> 33:47.483
Why do you smoke?

33:47.567 --> 33:49.736
You know smoking is,Â like,
really bad for you, right?

33:50.737 --> 33:53.156
And Dana was the one
that set fire to that abortion clinic.

33:53.239 --> 33:56.451
And now, we have helped her out
here and there over the years,

33:56.534 --> 33:59.370
but lately she--
she's been threatening us for more,

33:59.620 --> 34:01.164
which we don't have.

34:01.706 --> 34:02.999
So, we're trying to get rid of her.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.084
You were trying to kill her?

34:05.168 --> 34:06.669
Oh, Lord, Blair, no.

34:07.003 --> 34:08.546
We wanted her to get out of the country.

34:08.629 --> 34:09.547
God, and now she has your sister,

34:09.630 --> 34:11.215
and who knows where she's going
or what she's doing with her.

34:11.299 --> 34:13.509
Is she, like, dangerous?

34:13.593 --> 34:14.427
Yes.

34:15.762 --> 34:17.180
[sighs] In so many ways.

34:17.263 --> 34:18.306
Hey, hold the wheel.

34:18.806 --> 34:20.516
-My hair looks like hog shit.
-What?

34:20.600 --> 34:22.226
[tires rumbling]

34:22.310 --> 34:23.686
There. Yeah.

34:23.770 --> 34:25.063
Oh, that's cute, ain't it?

34:25.813 --> 34:26.939
[chuckles]

34:27.023 --> 34:27.940
Looks like yours.

34:28.024 --> 34:31.694
Okay, you're, like,
really starting to seriously freak me out.

34:31.778 --> 34:33.404
Oh, no, Muffin, don't be scared.

34:34.697 --> 34:36.324
I got a plan, all right?

34:38.034 --> 34:40.870
I'm just gonna quick
call my mom and check in, 'cause--

34:42.705 --> 34:43.539
Rude!

34:44.082 --> 34:46.834
How would you like it
if I threw out your belongings?

34:48.503 --> 34:49.378
Lord, girl.

34:51.672 --> 34:54.967
Hey! Hey! Do not touch my stuff!

34:55.927 --> 34:56.928
[exhales deeply]

34:57.011 --> 34:57.845
Now, you listen,

34:58.513 --> 35:00.181
I don't know what it was like
in your house growing up.

35:00.973 --> 35:03.851
You probably had everything you ever
wanted. No one ever told you no, huh?

35:04.477 --> 35:05.353
Well...

35:05.937 --> 35:07.772
your Aunt Dana does things different.

35:08.856 --> 35:10.817
I'm not all fancy like Debbie.

35:10.900 --> 35:11.901
[chuckles]

35:13.402 --> 35:14.529
[sighs] Damn.

35:14.987 --> 35:15.863
All right.

35:16.948 --> 35:17.824
Just...

35:19.659 --> 35:21.577
Just trust me, okay?

35:22.203 --> 35:24.163
You do exactly as I say...

35:26.916 --> 35:28.584
and everything will be just fine.

35:28.918 --> 35:31.337
My suspicions were correct.

35:31.420 --> 35:32.713
You were lying!

35:32.797 --> 35:35.383
You know, this is very traumatic,

35:35.466 --> 35:37.760
making me not trust my own instincts.

35:37.844 --> 35:41.139
-I am going to be in therapy for years!
-Okay, Blair.

35:41.222 --> 35:43.015
I'm gonna have to take a gap year,
at least!

35:45.768 --> 35:48.396
Okay, I know that it's very important
to find Sterling right now,

35:48.771 --> 35:50.314
but please don't forget,

35:50.690 --> 35:53.234
-I'm really super mad at you.
-Okay.

35:53.317 --> 35:54.944
No, we won't, we won't, we won't. Um...

35:55.486 --> 35:57.905
Debbie, just keep trying Dana
and I'm gonna try Sterling, okay.

35:57.989 --> 36:00.032
I am. Goshdang it,
she's still not picking up.

36:00.116 --> 36:01.409
I think we need to call the police.

36:02.702 --> 36:03.578
-But--
-No.

36:03.661 --> 36:05.371
There's no "buts." I'm calling the police.

36:05.454 --> 36:06.289
Wait, Anderson--

36:06.372 --> 36:07.498
Sterling is our daughter

36:07.582 --> 36:09.458
and I am calling the goddamn police!

36:12.795 --> 36:13.629
Okay.

36:26.142 --> 36:26.976
Hey.

36:27.935 --> 36:29.312
What are you doing here so late?

36:30.146 --> 36:31.272
You don't need it anymore?

36:32.481 --> 36:33.524
Do you want to come in?

36:33.608 --> 36:35.109
No, no. Here.

36:37.570 --> 36:38.946
Going out of town for a little bit.

36:39.363 --> 36:40.281
Maybe a while.

36:41.282 --> 36:42.116
Going where?

36:42.200 --> 36:43.117
Down to Florida.

36:43.701 --> 36:46.078
I reconnected with Tim, and Jordy,

36:46.162 --> 36:47.580
and D. Brad, and those guys.

36:48.581 --> 36:50.458
They got a couple of skips
I brought in before,

36:50.541 --> 36:51.500
they could use my help.

36:53.461 --> 36:55.546
-You know you left Florida for a reason.
-Yeah.

36:57.506 --> 36:58.716
What about Yogurtopia?

36:58.799 --> 37:00.384
I'm letting Miss Cathy take over.

37:00.468 --> 37:02.595
Yeah, she damn near fainted
when I told her,

37:02.678 --> 37:04.138
or she was just really tired.

37:06.265 --> 37:08.434
Are you coming back... to Atlanta?

37:09.602 --> 37:11.729
Just feel like
there isn't much here for me now.

37:11.812 --> 37:13.731
[scoffs] Guess I'm just chopped liver?

37:15.816 --> 37:16.943
You're with someone else.

37:19.779 --> 37:22.448
So, what? You're leaving?

37:22.907 --> 37:24.200
Because you got your feelings hurt?

37:25.201 --> 37:26.744
I thought we were friends.

37:26.827 --> 37:27.870
Ah, look, here...

37:28.621 --> 37:32.124
I'm leaving because
it's feeling like a dead end.

37:33.960 --> 37:34.877
What about your team?

37:34.961 --> 37:36.420
My teenage white saviors?

37:36.504 --> 37:38.339
Yeah, they're kind of your family now.

37:38.422 --> 37:40.383
They are not my family, okay?

37:40.466 --> 37:42.510
They're little girls
with attitude problems.

37:43.803 --> 37:44.929
Actually, that's just Blair,

37:45.012 --> 37:48.766
but they're annoying
and they ask too many questions,

37:48.849 --> 37:51.060
and they talk with their mouths full.

37:51.143 --> 37:52.645
If I have to listen to one more--

37:52.728 --> 37:54.313
[cell phone rings]

37:57.149 --> 37:57.984
Hello.

37:58.067 --> 38:00.319
[cell phone buzzes]

38:01.237 --> 38:02.363
[sighs] Shit.

38:03.656 --> 38:05.449
Hey. Got held up, but I'm on my way.

38:05.533 --> 38:06.867
-[Levi] You almost here?
-Yes.

38:06.951 --> 38:07.868
We gotta go!

38:07.952 --> 38:09.662
Yes, yes, yes, just be patient, baby.

38:13.457 --> 38:16.085
Hey, can we pull up at this rest stop?
I gotta pee real bad.

38:16.168 --> 38:17.753
No, don't have time. Hold it.

38:17.837 --> 38:19.130
Okay, I would hold it,

38:19.213 --> 38:22.133
but there's this guy, Declan Wright,
in Blair's study hall

38:22.216 --> 38:24.719
who held his pee
and his testicle exploded,

38:24.802 --> 38:27.430
which is weird because
urine is in the bladder,

38:27.513 --> 38:28.723
but that's what the doctor said.

38:29.015 --> 38:30.599
If you hold your pee
for a really long time

38:30.683 --> 38:31.934
your bladder actually expands,

38:32.018 --> 38:33.811
which at first sounds like
it would be a good thing

38:33.894 --> 38:35.896
because it's like, you know,
a greater surface area,

38:35.980 --> 38:38.316
greater ability to house a larger volume,

38:38.399 --> 38:41.068
but in actuality, it's, um-- uh...

38:41.652 --> 38:42.695
[Dana clears throat]

38:45.656 --> 38:47.074
Jeez, you're just like my mom.

38:49.201 --> 38:50.244
Okay, we're pulling over.

39:02.715 --> 39:04.925
Hey. Stay close, Muffin.

39:10.765 --> 39:12.975
Whoa. What the hell are you doing?
I thought you had to piss.

39:13.059 --> 39:14.143
[machine beeps]

39:14.226 --> 39:15.895
Oh, I do, but I'm also starving.

39:15.978 --> 39:18.397
It's been two hours since I ate
and I'm growing like a weed. [chuckles]

39:18.481 --> 39:20.191
I gotta have a snack,
something Sour Patch.

39:21.233 --> 39:22.568
That shit's disgusting.

39:29.909 --> 39:31.744
You know kids and their candy. [giggles]

39:33.871 --> 39:35.998
[sighs]
My mom would never let me get this much.

39:37.041 --> 39:38.876
Thank you, so much, Mom's sister.

39:38.959 --> 39:40.544
Aunt Dana. [chuckles]

39:40.628 --> 39:41.712
You're the best!

39:42.755 --> 39:44.173
-Thank you.
-Oh, yeah, well.

39:45.341 --> 39:46.175
Sure.

40:16.288 --> 40:18.374
[breathing deeply]

40:28.551 --> 40:31.262
Dear Lord, what up? It's me, again.

40:32.847 --> 40:34.390
I'm really scared right now,

40:34.473 --> 40:35.891
but I know you have a plan.

40:35.975 --> 40:37.143
[breathing deeply]

40:37.226 --> 40:40.479
Please help keep me
and the people I love safe.

40:41.313 --> 40:43.107
Please help me be brave.

40:43.691 --> 40:45.151
Please help me kick butt.

40:46.569 --> 40:49.029
And then, something for later,

40:49.447 --> 40:51.407
when I'm not being kidnapped anymore.

40:53.492 --> 40:55.202
Please help DanaÂ figure out

40:55.703 --> 40:58.831
how to have a peaceful, more happy life.

40:59.748 --> 41:01.375
It seems like she's got a lot of,Â like...

41:02.376 --> 41:03.419
problems.

41:05.171 --> 41:06.005
Okay.

41:06.130 --> 41:07.089
I think that's it.

41:08.215 --> 41:09.341
[exhales deeply] Amen.

41:10.092 --> 41:10.926
[sniffs]

41:11.302 --> 41:12.136
-Hey!
-[pounding]

41:13.012 --> 41:13.929
Come on.

41:14.263 --> 41:15.264
You done pissin'?

41:15.556 --> 41:17.475
Don't forget to wipe-- front to back.
All right?

41:18.058 --> 41:18.893
Come on.

41:20.060 --> 41:22.480
Oh, right. Uh, good idea. Wiping now.

41:25.191 --> 41:27.693
And she's been missing
for less than an hour?

41:28.152 --> 41:30.779
-[Debbie] Yes.
-Someone picked her up at the school

41:30.863 --> 41:33.032
in a gray pickup truck,

41:33.115 --> 41:37.036
uh, license plate GT9684J.

41:37.119 --> 41:38.829
-And how do you know that?
-It's our car.

41:40.873 --> 41:43.125
Do you have any ideas
about the person in question?

41:43.209 --> 41:45.252
Well, yes.

41:45.544 --> 41:46.670
It's her aunt.

41:48.714 --> 41:52.635
So, her aunt picked her up at school
in the family vehicle?

41:54.094 --> 41:55.554
I'm sorry, is there any reason to believe

41:55.638 --> 41:57.765
that this family member
is a danger to your daughter?

41:57.848 --> 41:58.682
Yes.

41:59.767 --> 42:01.143
[officer] Okay, what is it?

42:01.227 --> 42:03.437
Oh, um... You-- n-- n--

42:03.979 --> 42:06.273
-N-- Nothing specific comes to mind.
-[cell phone bleeps]

42:06.357 --> 42:09.652
[Anderson] Ju-- Just generally
kind of a bad influence.

42:10.194 --> 42:12.279
[Blair]
The text message came in at 10:32 p.m..

42:12.363 --> 42:14.490
The school is 1.2 miles northeast of here

42:14.573 --> 42:16.784
and based on the truck's
Peach Pass time stamps,

42:16.867 --> 42:19.662
they're heading southwest
of Atlanta on I-85.

42:19.745 --> 42:22.206
My guess is that they have
a 35 minute lead on us.

42:24.416 --> 42:25.292
Good work.

42:27.878 --> 42:29.046
I'm really good at this,

42:29.964 --> 42:31.840
-like a prodigy.
-Okay, stop annoying me.

42:32.341 --> 42:34.385
I've been checking
her Instagram and her TikTok,

42:34.468 --> 42:35.302
there's been nothing.

42:35.386 --> 42:38.639
I emailed her and I texted her,
like, 60 times and there's still nothing.

42:39.056 --> 42:40.432
[cell phone bleeps]

42:41.475 --> 42:43.352
Hey! Bank account!

42:44.061 --> 42:46.897
Sterling just used her debit card,
like, a bunch of times at

42:46.981 --> 42:51.610
G-A-V-E-N-R-S-3-4-2-1.

42:51.694 --> 42:52.528
What does that mean?

42:52.611 --> 42:54.280
VEN: vending machine.

42:54.363 --> 42:56.115
RS: rest stop. Look up those numbers.

42:56.198 --> 42:57.533
Okay... Um...

42:59.326 --> 43:01.370
-It's right off Hawkins Ridge!
-Hold on.

43:01.453 --> 43:03.122
-[tires screech]
-[Blair screams]

43:05.124 --> 43:06.417
[horns honk]

43:18.887 --> 43:19.972
[gasps]

43:20.055 --> 43:21.181
Sour Patch Kids!

43:21.265 --> 43:23.475
Sterling hates them,
but she knows I love them,

43:23.559 --> 43:25.477
even when they cut my mouth up
like little razor blades.

43:25.561 --> 43:26.395
It's a sign.

43:27.688 --> 43:29.023
[door opens]

43:33.736 --> 43:34.612
Sterl--

43:36.196 --> 43:37.615
Hey, hey, message.

43:38.240 --> 43:42.244
"Dana, Mom's twin. Levi, white man,
croc tat, forties."

43:42.494 --> 43:44.330
"I-L-Y-S-M-S."

43:45.039 --> 43:47.583
License plate. I can run this
through the Georgia registry.

43:47.666 --> 43:50.169
Then we can do Florida and Alabama
if we come up short.

43:50.753 --> 43:54.340
No, "I love you so much, Sis."

43:55.257 --> 43:56.216
[sighs]

43:57.926 --> 44:00.137
-What--?
-Okay, kid. No, no, no, no, no...

44:00.304 --> 44:02.014
We're gonna get her, okay?

44:02.473 --> 44:04.683
Come on. Come on. Come on.

44:05.142 --> 44:06.185
-We're gonna get her.
-Okay.

44:06.268 --> 44:07.519
-All right? Let's go.
-Okay.

44:10.981 --> 44:12.399
We gotta dig up those names.

44:12.733 --> 44:14.151
Only cops can do that, right?

44:14.234 --> 44:15.694
Stop saying stuff I know.

44:16.028 --> 44:17.863
So, we need to talk to somebody
who knows cops, right?

44:17.946 --> 44:19.031
I said, stop saying stuff I know.

44:19.615 --> 44:20.616
Get in the car.

44:24.495 --> 44:26.080
Hey, my man, Bowser.

44:26.163 --> 44:28.248
Look, I got a lot of hits on that vid.

44:28.332 --> 44:29.208
No hard feelings, right?

44:29.291 --> 44:31.669
Yeah, my feelings are not hard.
Just give me the info, Terrance.

44:31.752 --> 44:35.381
Okay, my man, Arnold,
from the 16th Precinct hooked me up.

44:35.464 --> 44:38.425
What do we have here?
Nothing on a Dana Culpepper.

44:38.509 --> 44:39.927
Nada, zip.

44:40.010 --> 44:41.345
It's like she's a ghost or something,

44:41.428 --> 44:45.265
but I do have a record
on a white male, Levi, in his forties

44:45.349 --> 44:47.142
with a crocodile tattoo on his neck.

44:47.643 --> 44:50.312
Levi Yates, 44, brown hair.

44:50.396 --> 44:51.522
Ooh, he's been busy.

44:51.605 --> 44:54.358
What do we have here?
We got trespassing, B and E,

44:54.775 --> 44:55.859
aggravated assault,

44:55.943 --> 44:58.445
assault again, drug possession,

44:58.904 --> 45:00.781
two attempts to traffic over the border,

45:00.864 --> 45:02.157
and the list goes on.

45:02.241 --> 45:03.742
You got a last known address?

45:03.826 --> 45:07.162
Bluebird RV Park,
13 West Alpharetta Parkway,

45:07.246 --> 45:08.414
out in the middle of nowhere.

45:08.497 --> 45:09.665
That's out by 141.

45:10.040 --> 45:11.625
Makes sense
with the direction they're heading in.

45:11.709 --> 45:13.293
Dana's going to pick him up.

45:13.377 --> 45:14.336
Yep, all right.

45:14.420 --> 45:15.879
Hey, Terrance, um...

45:16.630 --> 45:17.464
thank you.

45:17.548 --> 45:18.674
Oh, you got it, my man.

45:18.757 --> 45:20.884
Anything you need, just let me know.

45:22.136 --> 45:23.220
Besides my girlfriend.

45:23.303 --> 45:24.596
Yeah, okay. Jesus.

45:25.723 --> 45:27.433
-[cell phone rings]
-Oh, God.

45:29.768 --> 45:32.146
-Hi, Mom.
-God, where the heck are you, sweetie?

45:32.813 --> 45:33.981
Are you out of your mind?

45:34.064 --> 45:36.150
-Your sister is missing and we--
-Yeah, no duh.

45:36.233 --> 45:38.694
-Hey!
-Sorry, I didn't mean to sass you,

45:38.777 --> 45:42.322
but Mom, the guy who Sterling
and I work for, Mr.Â Bowser,

45:42.406 --> 45:45.159
he's been helping me track Sterling
through the truck's Peach Pass

45:45.242 --> 45:46.410
and Sterling's bank account,

45:46.493 --> 45:48.495
and we think we know where they're headed.

45:49.538 --> 45:51.707
-Oh, Blair--
-Mom, you have to trust me on this.

45:52.040 --> 45:53.500
I'll text you the address, okay?

45:53.584 --> 45:54.543
No, just wait--

45:54.626 --> 45:55.627
[disconnect tone]

45:55.711 --> 45:56.628
[groans]

45:57.421 --> 45:59.214
-[sighs]
-[cell phone bleeps]

45:59.298 --> 46:01.300
[male police officer]
You said she's dangerous.

46:01.383 --> 46:02.468
What do you mean by that?

46:03.552 --> 46:04.386
Ma'am?

46:04.636 --> 46:06.638
We have a few questions
about the person of interest.

46:06.722 --> 46:10.476
Sure, you know, if I could just have
one moment with my husband.

46:10.559 --> 46:12.311
-[chuckles and clears throat]
-Excuse me.

46:15.189 --> 46:16.899
Oh, God. Oh.

46:16.982 --> 46:18.650
I know where Dana may be taking Sterling.

46:19.276 --> 46:20.402
-We have to go.
-Okay.

46:21.069 --> 46:21.904
Oh.

46:23.113 --> 46:25.616
-All right, go. Let's just go. Quietly.
-[person clears throat]

46:32.372 --> 46:34.249
[Anderson] Yee-haw!

46:34.333 --> 46:36.251
-[chuckling] Heck, yeah!
-[Debbie] Oh! Anderson!

46:36.752 --> 46:37.586
[tires screech]

46:44.843 --> 46:46.512
[buzzer sounds]

46:52.726 --> 46:54.102
This is where you're from.

46:55.437 --> 46:56.396
Your roots.

46:57.940 --> 46:59.566
Your mama's been
trying to hide it from you,

46:59.650 --> 47:02.110
but Aunt Dana's here to show you
where you really come from.

47:03.946 --> 47:05.906
This could have been you in another life.

47:18.210 --> 47:19.169
Hey, baby.

47:20.045 --> 47:21.171
What the hell is this?

47:21.255 --> 47:22.381
Sterling, meet Levi.

47:22.798 --> 47:24.007
You got Sterling.

47:24.091 --> 47:25.425
Pleased to make your acquaintance.

47:25.843 --> 47:27.469
Dana, this was not part of the plan.

47:27.970 --> 47:31.598
Oh, well, if it's too much trouble,
then I'm happy to be on my way.

47:31.682 --> 47:32.724
You know what, I'll just hoof it.

47:32.808 --> 47:35.269
Don't worry about driving me.
Aunt Dana. I will see you at Christmas.

47:35.352 --> 47:36.770
No.

47:37.145 --> 47:38.230
No.

47:39.314 --> 47:41.775
I'm good at adapting to new situations.

47:42.901 --> 47:45.362
Since you went and made this decision
all by your little self...

47:45.445 --> 47:46.321
Oh, come on.

47:46.405 --> 47:47.614
I got a better idea.

47:48.240 --> 47:49.700
We're gonna ask for more money.

47:49.783 --> 47:50.659
Money from who?

47:51.535 --> 47:52.911
From the Richie Rich Wesleys.

47:53.579 --> 47:54.621
You made a dumb bitch move,

47:54.705 --> 47:57.374
but you stumbled
into a golden goose opportunity.

48:02.212 --> 48:03.714
Shit, the gate's locked.

48:09.386 --> 48:10.304
All right.

48:11.555 --> 48:12.639
[screams]

48:14.850 --> 48:15.851
[both laugh]

48:15.934 --> 48:18.312
-[Levi] What the hell was that?
-Help! I'm in here!

48:18.395 --> 48:19.479
Shut it, blondie.

48:19.688 --> 48:21.899
Do not call her that.
It's our thing, baby.

48:22.733 --> 48:26.862
Come on, let's just put that gun down
and talk about it, all right?

48:26.945 --> 48:29.448
And how do you suggest
I handle this situation, huh?

48:29.531 --> 48:30.365
Back off.

48:30.449 --> 48:33.035
I will not stand for you
putting Sterling at risk.

48:33.118 --> 48:34.620
You're all confident today.

48:35.287 --> 48:37.497
